.TH "bio_integrity_alloc" 9 "bio_integrity_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bio_integrity_alloc \- Allocate integrity payload and attach it to bio
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct bio_integrity_payload *" bio_integrity_alloc
.BI "(struct bio *bio "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_mask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nr_vecs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bio" 12
bio to attach integrity metadata to
.IP "gfp_mask" 12
Memory allocation mask
.IP "nr_vecs" 12
Number of integrity metadata scatter-gather elements
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function prepares a bio for attaching integrity
metadata.  nr_vecs specifies the maximum number of pages containing
integrity metadata that can be attached.
